    "invithelp":{
      "title1": "About Invitation",
      "title2": "Invite a person to share the collaborative tools of the portal",
      "title3": "How to invite a collaborator",
      "text1": "This service allows you to invite a person who does not belong to the French mathematical community to the Online Mathematics Platform (PLM). Once the invitation is validated by your collaborator, you will be able to add him/her to your collaborative projects accessible on this portal: PlmBox, SVN/GIT, Pad (coming soon), ShareLaTex (coming soon), etc.",
      "text2": "If the person you wish to collaborate with is in an INSMI unit (permanent or not), suggest that he/she create an account on this portal instead (by clicking on Connection then Get an account on the PLM accessible from his/her Profile).",
      "text3": "Please note: these accounts do not give access to the electronic documentation proposed on this site.",
      "li1": "The form above allows you to check if your future collaborator does not already have a valid access.",
      "li2": "If this is not the case, fill in the name, first name and email (preferably institutional) and validate the invitation.",
      "li3": "Then, this person will have to accept the invitation received by email, choose his login and password.",
      "li4": "Once this is done, you will be able to find them (with their login) in the My Guests tab and use their login to add them to your projects."
    },
